    • nearToLineSegment

      public boolean nearToLineSegment(Vector3Int a, Vector3Int b, int maxDist)
      Check if the point specified (by the first two components of) this 3D-vector is not farther away than a set maximum distance from the line segment spanned between two points.

      The point must be reachable by a line orthogonal to the line segment, which starts within the line segment - i.e., we are not considering the infinite line going through the two points.

      Another way to look at this restriction, is that the three points form a triangle without obtuse angle.

      Parameters:
      a - One endpoint of the line segment.
      b - One endpoint of the line segment.
      maxDist - Maximal distance this point may have to the line segment.
      Returns:
      True iff the point was close to the finite line segment.
